  osef: 
  textboxStart:
  - Since Card Break is determined by the card value, playing low value is risky.
  - However the lower the value, the higher the damage.
  - Card with a value of 1 will do more damage than a value of 2, and a 2 will do
    more damage than a 3, etc...
  - In general, for the same attack, the damage of a card with a value of 1 is twice
    the damage of a card with a value of 9.
  - A good strategy for capitalizing on this, is to "confirm" that you have hit an
    opponent with a high value card before playing low value card.
  textboxEnd:
  - 'It requires a heavier execution, as you have to cycle through your deck in-between
    your attacks. '
  - So don't worry if you struggle with this, it's only for optimizing your damage.
  comboNotes:
  - Land a hit
  - Play card 1
  - Play card 1
